<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">White Cloud Temple</ENAMEX>
Beijing‚Äôs most active <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC">Daoist</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">complex</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">Bai Yun Guan</ENAMEX>, is better known as <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">White Cloud Temple</ENAMEX>. This is also the capital‚Äôs most fascinating religious <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">site</ENAMEX>, a place of superstition and incense, mystery and spirited worship. As <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">China‚</ENAMEX>Äôs leading indigenous religion, <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">Daoism</ENAMEX> differs from <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Buddhism</ENAMEX> (transplanted from <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">India</ENAMEX>) not so much in the architecture of its temples and the art of its statuary (these are often quite similar in style) as in its practices and beliefs. <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Daoism</ENAMEX> emphasized nature, the <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">individual</ENAMEX>, and the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Way</ENAMEX>, but in its organized form it relies on a huge <ENAMEX TYPE="WORK_OF_ART">pantheon of gods</ENAMEX>, goddesses, and supernatural icons promising miracles.
